cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.LO 

The paper discusses a development methodology for concurrent software, which suggests that it could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper explores the potential of choreographic programming by writing concurrent algorithms for sorting, solving linear equations, and computing Fast Fourier Transforms, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the lessons learned from the experiment, which suggests that it could also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
